-- Chilean Stocks: Azul Azul, Cencosud, Lan Airlines Were Active
-- B y   E d u a r d o   T h o m s o n
-- 2012-06-22T21:23:44Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-06-22/chilean-stocks-azul-azul-cencosud-and-lan-airlines-are-active.html
The following companies had  unusual 
price changes in Chilean trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses, and prices are as of the close.  The  Ipsa index  retreated 0.1 percent to 4,358.84. The  MSCI
Chile index  dropped 1.3 percent to 2,353.99.  Azul Azul SA (AZUL)  , owner of the  Universidad de Chile 
soccer team, slumped 9 percent to 1,396.3 pesos and earlier fell
as much as 15 percent. Universidad de Chile lost to Argentina’s
Boca Juniors in the semifinals of the Libertadores Cup.  Cencosud SA (CENCOSUD)   retreated 1.1 percent to 2,765.7
pesos, the lowest in a week. Chile’s largest retailer by sales
priced 91.3 million new shares at 2,600 pesos each, as part of a
larger sale of 243 million new shares.  Lan Airlines SA (LAN)   fell 1.1 percent to 13,489 pesos.
The Chilean carrier completed its takeover of Brazil’s Tam SA,
changing its name to Latam Airlines Group SA.  Fitch Ratings  cut
its debt rating for the newly combined company to BB+, one level
below investment grade.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Eduardo Thomson in Santiago at 
